<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uevilrulz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evilrulz</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Toede Slavedriver</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>20</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>3/8/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>9:23:24 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: current situation..</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Please explain to me why inviting people from no posting guilds hurts the system in anyway.<br>
<br>
1. By inviteing these guys to loot they have less and less of a reason to apply for calendar rights thus lessening the amount of guilds that post.<br>
<br>
2. If a guild disbands to piggyback good. If 10 guilds did this the the posting number would go from 30 guilds to 20. The calendar exists cause too many guilds are planable. The less that post the better. The most guilds that get equipped w/o posting rights the less future posting guilds youll have. <br>
<br>
3. With the number required for posting rights moved up to 40 from 18 the chance that a guild is inviting these extras out of need is slim to none. I can understand this rule when posting required 18 but not 40...<br>
<br>
<br>
The rules do state that a god must die and that responsibility fall on the posting entity. Cazic didnt die and the rules state thats our problem. I accept that and feel 30 days w/ loss of posting rights is justified. Whether Bots said they would be there and cancelled may be lame but it is the rules.<br>
<br>
Losing posting of a raid we already had scheduled for no reason isnt fair. Admins and ex-admins are disagreeing on what the 6 person rule states. And if people spent the extra 30 seconds to read the next line it states exactly what violates the 6 per guild invite. None of which we broke. Since no one reads that far ill post it..<br>
<br>
<br>
Intent: This was probably the hardest rule to nail down. Please read this intent part very carefully so that you understand what the violations are.<br>
Of course you may invite friends on raids. Because you need the class, because they are good friends, because you need help, or because you don't want loot to rot. What you may NOT do is use your relationship with another posting entity so that you all may go twice per round. If you have another guild you are always teaming with, you need to form an alliance and in this way you are only entitled to one day per round, like everyone else. Also in this way one guild may not be used as a front for another guild. If you have ANY questions, or need ANY clarifications I highly recommend posting them early. The more serious the violation the more serious the penalty, and trust me this will be the rule most closely watched. <br>
<br>
<br>
Please show me in there what part of the rule we violated. If you do then ill be amazed.<br>
<br>
<br>
What I do find funny though is the rules state if you cant kill a god you must call the BB. But also states its the reserving guilds job to make sure the god dies, kinda a catch 22. The reserving guild is callin in the BB because they cant kill the god. BB is there cause they have proven there &quot;uberness&quot; BB declines now your putting the rule of killin a god back on the guild that has admitted they cant.</font><P><P><i><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uevilrulz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evilrulz</A> at: 3/8/01 9:28:13 pm</FONT><br></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unagellom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nagellom</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Wog</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>28</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>3/9/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>6:57:27 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/litlebegeo/anage.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: current situation..</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Have you been reading the thread?</font><P><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=3 COLOR=#9f9f5f>
